            <title>[PIG-2479] changingPattern should be used with checkmodified in ivysettings.xml</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PIG-2479</link>
                <project id="12310730" key="PIG">Pig</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In ivy/ivysettings.xml, checkmodified=&quot;true&quot; is used for the apache-snapshots resolver. When using checkmodified=&quot;true&quot;, you also need changingPattern=&quot;.*SNAPSHOT&quot; (in this case - it&apos;s Ivy, so theoretically that could be anything, but since the modified jars here would all be Maven-produced, they&apos;ll all have versions ending in &quot;SNAPSHOT&quot;) or they won&apos;t actually be checked.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In addition, it&apos;d be nice to have checkmodified=&quot;true&quot; and changingPattern=&quot;.*SNAPSHOT&quot; on the &quot;fs&quot; resolver, so that you can build against locally built SNAPSHOTs of dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
